    {
      "question": "If two positive integers $a$ and $b$ are written as $a = x^3 y^2$ and $b = x y^3$, where $x$ and $y$ are prime numbers, then the result of $\\text{HCF}(a, b) \\times \\text{LCM}(a, b)$ is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recall the property that the product of two numbers is equal to the product of their HCF and LCM.",
          "Calculate the product $a \\times b$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\text{HCF}(a, b) \\times \\text{LCM}(a, b) = a \\times b$ \\\\ $a \\times b = (x^3 y^2) \\times (x y^3) = x^{3+1} y^{2+3} = x^4 y^5$"
      },
      "topic": "Real Numbers",
      "subtopic": "HCF and LCM",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
      "options": [
        "(A) $x^3 y^3$",
        "(B) $x^4 y^4$",
        "(C) $x^4 y^5$",
        "(D) $x^2 y^2$"
      ],
